# =============================================================================
# Hybrid Anti-Brain-Wiki .gitignore
# Policy: AWF 4.1 Eternal Context Design + ABW runtime state separation
# =============================================================================

# --- .brain/ runtime state (NEVER commit) ---
# Per AWF save_brain.md: session.json is always local state
.brain/session.json
.brain/session_log.txt
.brain/cache/

# ABW runtime state -- generated at runtime by ingest-wiki, query-wiki, lint-wiki
# Examples in templates/ -- these files start EMPTY and are populated by skills
.brain/grounding_queue.json
.brain/knowledge_gaps.json
.brain/deliberation_runs.jsonl
.brain/lessons_learned.jsonl
.brain/exit_gate_policy.json
.brain/circuit_breaker.json
.brain/resume_state.json
.brain/continuation_backlog.json
.brain/locked_decisions.json
.brain/unsafe_zones.json
.brain/continuation_policy.json
.brain/handover_log.jsonl
.brain/step_history.jsonl
.brain/active_execution.json
.brain/model_claims.jsonl

# Bootstrap reasoning state (do not commit greenfield assumptions/plans)
.brain/bootstrap/*.json
.brain/bootstrap/*.jsonl

# --- .brain/ files that MAY be committed ---
# .brain/brain.json         -> Commit if team shares project knowledge (AWF policy)
# .brain/snapshots/         -> Optional: commit for historical record
# .brain/summaries/         -> Optional: commit for human-readable context
# .brain/.gitkeep files     -> Always commit (preserve directory structure)

# --- processed/ runtime data ---
# manifest.jsonl is append-only runtime state. Each project generates its own.
processed/manifest.jsonl

# --- raw/ source files ---
# Raw sources may be large (PDFs, videos). Decide per-project.
# Uncomment below if raw files should not be committed:
# raw/*
# !raw/.gitkeep

# --- wiki/ lint reports (generated output) ---
wiki/_indexes/lint-report-*.md

# --- notebooks/ packages (runtime output) ---
notebooks/packages/

# --- OS and IDE artifacts ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# --- Node/Python artifacts (if applicable) ---
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.env
.env.local
